==English==

===Noun===
'''truck''' (''plural:'' '''trucks''')

#(''especially US'') A large vehicle designed for carrying heavy cargo. 
#A [[wagon]].
#A [[cart]].
#A [[pantechnicon]].
#The part of a [[skateboard]] that joins the wheels to the deck, usually mounted with a raiser in between.
#Business, trade.
#The ball on top of a [[flagpole]].
# {{nautical}} On a wooden [[mast]], a circular disc of wood at the top of the mast, usually with holes or [[sheaves]] to [[reeve]] signal [[halyard]]s.
# {{nautical}} The wheel of a [[gun-carriage]].

====Synonyms====
*(large vehicle designed for carrying heavy cargo): [[lorry]] (''British'')

